  "extra": {
    "ds": {
      "scale": 0.8,
      "offset": [200, -100]
    },
    "description": "FrameWeaver Temporal Control v2 — Intra-scene prompt variation within a single LTX 2.3 generation.\n\nBased on PromptRelay reference workflow (prompt_relay_ltx23_test_02.json).\n\nCorrect LTX 2.3 chain:\n  UNETLoader → SageAttention → FW_TemporalPromptEncode → LTX2PreviewOverride → SamplerCustom\n  Positive → LTXVConditioning.positive + ConditioningZeroOut → LTXVConditioning.negative\n\nUsage:\n1. UNETLoader: Load LTX 2.3 transformer (ltx-2.3-22b-distilled)\n2. DualCLIPLoader: Load Gemma 3 + LTX text projection\n3. VAELoaderKJ: Load LTX 2.3 video VAE\n4. FW_StyleAnchor: Define persistent style + character identity\n5. FW_ScenePromptEvolver (syntax_mode=smart): Write block-header prompts\n   Example:\n     Scene 1:\n     An old man walks through a mystical forest\n     Scene 2:\n     He stops and looks around nervously\n     Scene 3:\n     He breaks into a run\n6. FW_ContinuityEncoder: Blends style + scene prompt\n7. FW_TemporalPromptEncode: Core temporal encoding\n   - global_prompt: from ContinuityEncoder (auto-connected)\n   - local_prompts: pipe-delimited sub-actions\n   - segment_lengths: comma-delimited frame counts (must sum to latent frames)\n   - epsilon: 0.001 = sharp boundaries, 0.5+ = soft transitions\n8. ConditioningZeroOut: Creates zeroed negative from positive\n9. LTXVConditioning: Merges positive+negative for sampler\n10. SamplerCustom: Runs the generation\n11. VAEDecode → VHS_VideoCombine: Output video\n\nOptional: Connect FW_RelayOptions → FW_TemporalPromptEncode.relay_options for per-stream tuning."
  },
  "version": 0.4
}
